title: Story Starter by selfStarter VOICE EDUCATION
details: Help your child become a self starter! Just teach them to say, "Alexa, open Story Starter" then say "Student," and Alexa will give them a daily writing prompt. Educational exercises initiated by students can help them become independent learners, while at the same time, developing confidence in their ability to finish assignments.  After your child writes their response to the writing prompt, have them give it to you, and at your own leisure say, "Alexa, open Story Starter." Choose the "Teacher" option, and Alexa will read the teacher's guide for the daily writing prompt so you can review your student's work. If you have a pre-writer, have them dictate their answer to you, and use some or all of what you wrote down as an opportunity for them to do copy work. Dictation and copy work exercises will build reading, writing, and grammar skills.This is the first Skill by selfStarter: VOICE EDUCATION. Go to https://selfstarter.io for more info about how to use this Skill, and for tips on how you can help your child become a self starter!

details: Jim Harold interviews authors and experts on true crime cases. Past guests have included a Pulitzer Prize winner and Best Selling authors. Here are a few quick tips when navigating our skill. First thing to note, when opening the skill you’ll be offered the latest episode, but if that’s not what you’re looking for, you can always find something more specific. This skill allows you to skip forward and backward by entire episodes, and you can also fast forward and rewind within episodes themselves. In addition, you can ask the skill to play the newest or oldest episodes released; or if you want to get specific, play a specific episode by saying the episode number. Try some of these commands:**Skip Entire Episodes**— [While Episode Is Playing] = “Alexa skip” or “Alexa tell Crime Scene to skip ahead 5 episodes”**Fast Forward/Back Within Episode**— [While Episode Is Playing] = “Alexa, tell Crime Scene to fast forward 2 minutes”— [While Episode Is Playing] = “Alexa, tell Crime Scene to rewind 45 seconds”**Select Newest Episode**— “Alexa, tell Crime Scene to play the newest episode”

title: Beautiful Piano: Relaxing Sound
details: Beautiful Piano music is a perfect background sound for studying, working, reading or writing. It helps to concentrate, relieve stress and improve productivity.How to use "Beautiful Piano: Relaxing Sound"?You can say:- "Alexa, open Beautiful Piano"- "Alexa, start Beautiful Piano"- "Alexa, play Beautiful Piano"It will automatically play the sound indefinitely until you say "Alexa, stop".How to set a timer?First, you need to play the sound using one of the above method. Then, you can limit the time the sound will play by saying "Alexa, stop playing in 1 hour" (or however long you want it to last). Once 1 hour has passed, the sound will stop playing.How to support us?Your review is extremely important and it shows us your support. Please consider leaving a review if you love the skill. Your review encourages us to continue making more skills.Listen to more relaxing sounds?You can search in the Alexa Skill store the following skills:- Zen Spa- Forest Birdsong- Forest Birds- Study Music- Zen Meditation- Beautiful Piano- Forest Campfire- Stress Relief- Tropical Birds- Waves Sandy Beach- Morning Tweet Tweet- Focus Music- Cave Water Drips- Public Park- Tribal Festival

title: Podcast Junkies
example.1: “Alexa, tell Podcast Junkies to play the newest episode”
example.2: “Alexa, tell Podcast Junkies to go back 5 episodes”
example.3: “Alexa, tell Podcast Junkies to fast forward 2 minutes”
details: Podcast Junkies was born out of a genuine interest in and curiosity for this growing league of podcast hosts. It's hosted by Harry Duran. It features wide-ranging, authentic and sometimes candid interviews with this family of voices behind the microphone. The shows themselves cover a variety of topics such as Business, Finance Entrepreneurism, History, Comedy, Storytelling and more. Podcast Junkies explores the motivations behind the podcast's inception and allows the listener to connect on a more personal level with some of their favorite hosts.Here are a few quick tips when navigating our skill. First thing to note, when opening the skill you’ll be offered the latest episode, but if that’s not what you’re looking for, you can always find something more specific. This skill allows you to skip forward and backward by entire episodes, and you can also fast forward and rewind within episodes themselves. In addition, you can ask the skill to play the newest or oldest episodes released; or if you want to get specific, play a specific episode by saying the episode number. Try some of these commands:**Skip Entire Episodes**— [While Episode Is Playing] = “Alexa skip” or “Alexa tell Podcast Junkies to skip ahead 5 episodes”**Fast Forward/Back Within Episode**— [While Episode Is Playing] = “Alexa, tell Podcast Junkies to fast forward 2 minutes”— [While Episode Is Playing] = “Alexa, tell Podcast Junkies to rewind 45 seconds”**Select Newest Episode**— “Alexa, tell Podcast Junkies to play the newest episode”
